---
import PatternLayout from '../../../../layouts/PatternLayout.astro';

const testimonialStyles = `.testimonials {
  padding: var(--size-2xl) var(--size-l);
}

.testimonials-header {
  text-align: center;
  max-width: 60ch;
  margin-inline: auto;
}

.testimonials-header .lead {
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
}

.testimonial {
  margin: 0;
  padding: var(--size-l);
  background: var(--color-surface-raised);
  border-radius: var(--radius-l);
}

.testimonial p {
  font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
  font-style: italic;
  color: var(--color-text);
  margin: 0;
}

.testimonial footer {
  margin-top: var(--size-m);
  padding-top: var(--size-m);
  border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
}

.testimonial cite {
  font-style: normal;
}

.testimonial .author-name {
  display: block;
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
  color: var(--color-text);
}

.testimonial .author-role {
  display: block;
  font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
}`;

const carouselStyles = `.testimonial-carousel {
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--size-l);
  overflow-x: auto;
  scroll-snap-type: x mandatory;
  scrollbar-width: none;
  padding: var(--size-s) 0;
}

.testimonial-carousel::-webkit-scrollbar {
  display: none;
}

.testimonial-carousel > * {
  flex: 0 0 min(500px, 85vw);
  scroll-snap-align: center;
}`;

const starRatingStyles = `.star-rating {
  color: var(--color-warning);
}`;
---

<PatternLayout
  title="Testimonial Patterns"
  description="Testimonial section patterns for landing pages and marketing sites. Quote cards, avatar grids, and carousel layouts."
  patternName="Testimonials"
  category="marketing"
  currentPath="/docs/patterns/marketing/testimonials/"
>
  <section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Testimonials are essential for building credibility on marketing pages. These patterns use semantic <code>&lt;blockquote&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;cite&gt;</code> elements for proper quote attribution, combined with <code>&lt;layout-grid&gt;</code> for responsive card layouts.</p>
      <p><strong>Key features:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Semantic HTML with <code>blockquote</code> and <code>cite</code></li>
        <li>Responsive grid layouts with <code>layout-grid</code></li>
        <li>Avatar integration with <code>user-avatar</code></li>
        <li>Star ratings with <code>icon-wc</code></li>
        <li>CSS scroll-snap carousel for featured testimonials</li>
        <li>Accessible by default</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Simple Quotes</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>The most straightforward testimonial pattern: quote cards with author attribution. Uses <code>layout-grid</code> for a responsive layout that automatically adjusts columns based on available space.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/patterns/demos/testimonials-quotes.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/testimonials-quotes"
      title="Simple Quotes"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" label="Simple testimonial quotes">&lt;section class="testimonials"&gt;
  &lt;layout-center data-max-width="wide"&gt;
    &lt;layout-stack data-gap="2xl"&gt;
      &lt;div class="testimonials-header"&gt;
        &lt;layout-stack data-gap="s"&gt;
          &lt;h2&gt;What our customers say&lt;/h2&gt;
          &lt;p class="lead"&gt;Hear from teams who have transformed their development workflow.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;layout-grid data-min="300px" data-gap="l"&gt;
        &lt;blockquote class="testimonial"&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;"This framework has completely changed how we build interfaces. We shipped our redesign in half the time."&lt;/p&gt;
          &lt;footer&gt;
            &lt;cite&gt;
              &lt;span class="author-name"&gt;Sarah Chen&lt;/span&gt;
              &lt;span class="author-role"&gt;Engineering Lead, TechCorp&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/cite&gt;
          &lt;/footer&gt;
        &lt;/blockquote&gt;
        &lt;blockquote class="testimonial"&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;"The semantic HTML approach means our sites are accessible by default."&lt;/p&gt;
          &lt;footer&gt;
            &lt;cite&gt;
              &lt;span class="author-name"&gt;Marcus Johnson&lt;/span&gt;
              &lt;span class="author-role"&gt;Senior Developer, StartupXYZ&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/cite&gt;
          &lt;/footer&gt;
        &lt;/blockquote&gt;
        &lt;blockquote class="testimonial"&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;"No build step, no complex configuration. We went from idea to production in record time."&lt;/p&gt;
          &lt;footer&gt;
            &lt;cite&gt;
              &lt;span class="author-name"&gt;Elena Rodriguez&lt;/span&gt;
              &lt;span class="author-role"&gt;CTO, WebAgency&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/cite&gt;
          &lt;/footer&gt;
        &lt;/blockquote&gt;
      &lt;/layout-grid&gt;
    &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
  &lt;/layout-center&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>With Avatars and Ratings</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Enhanced testimonials featuring author avatars and star ratings. The <code>user-avatar</code> component displays profile images, while <code>icon-wc</code> renders star ratings.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/patterns/demos/testimonials-avatars.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/testimonials-avatars"
      title="Testimonials with Avatars"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" label="Testimonials with avatars and star ratings">&lt;layout-grid data-min="300px" data-gap="l"&gt;
  &lt;blockquote class="testimonial"&gt;
    &lt;layout-stack data-gap="m"&gt;
      &lt;layout-cluster class="star-rating" data-gap="xs"&gt;
        &lt;icon-wc name="star" size="sm"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
        &lt;icon-wc name="star" size="sm"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
        &lt;icon-wc name="star" size="sm"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
        &lt;icon-wc name="star" size="sm"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
        &lt;icon-wc name="star" size="sm"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
      &lt;/layout-cluster&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;"The layout primitives are incredibly powerful. We've built complex dashboards with minimal custom CSS."&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;footer&gt;
        &lt;layout-cluster data-gap="s" data-align="center"&gt;
          &lt;user-avatar data-size="lg"&gt;
            &lt;img src="user-photo.jpg" alt="" /&gt;
          &lt;/user-avatar&gt;
          &lt;cite&gt;
            &lt;span class="author-name"&gt;Alex Thompson&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;span class="author-role"&gt;Lead Developer, DataFlow&lt;/span&gt;
          &lt;/cite&gt;
        &lt;/layout-cluster&gt;
      &lt;/footer&gt;
    &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
  &lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;/layout-grid&gt;</code-block>

    <h3>Star Rating CSS</h3>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Add this style for the star rating color:</p>
    </layout-text>

    <code-block language="css" label="Star rating styles">{starRatingStyles}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Carousel</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>A horizontally scrolling carousel with CSS scroll-snap for featured testimonials. Larger cards with more prominent quotes. The carousel scrolls naturally with touch/mouse and snaps to each testimonial.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/patterns/demos/testimonials-carousel.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/testimonials-carousel"
      title="Testimonial Carousel"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" label="Testimonial carousel with scroll-snap">&lt;section class="testimonials"&gt;
  &lt;layout-center data-max-width="wide"&gt;
    &lt;layout-stack data-gap="l"&gt;
      &lt;div class="testimonials-header"&gt;
        &lt;layout-stack data-gap="s"&gt;
          &lt;h2&gt;Loved by teams everywhere&lt;/h2&gt;
          &lt;p class="lead"&gt;See what developers are saying about their experience.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class="testimonial-carousel"&gt;
        &lt;blockquote class="testimonial"&gt;
          &lt;layout-stack data-gap="m"&gt;
            &lt;span class="quote-icon"&gt;
              &lt;icon-wc name="quote" size="xl"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
            &lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;p class="testimonial-quote"&gt;"The shift to semantic HTML has made our codebase so much cleaner. Junior developers can understand and contribute immediately."&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;footer&gt;
              &lt;layout-cluster data-gap="s" data-align="center"&gt;
                &lt;user-avatar data-size="xl"&gt;
                  &lt;img src="user-photo.jpg" alt="" /&gt;
                &lt;/user-avatar&gt;
                &lt;cite&gt;
                  &lt;span class="author-name"&gt;David Park&lt;/span&gt;
                  &lt;span class="author-role"&gt;Engineering Manager, TechVenture&lt;/span&gt;
                &lt;/cite&gt;
              &lt;/layout-cluster&gt;
            &lt;/footer&gt;
          &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
        &lt;/blockquote&gt;
        &lt;!-- Additional testimonials... --&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
  &lt;/layout-center&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;</code-block>

    <h3>Carousel CSS</h3>
